The '''[[Alecu Russo]] Balti State University''' ([[Romanian language|Romanian]]: ''Universitatea de Stat "Alecu Russo" din Bălți'') is the [[Education in Moldova|second biggest university in Moldova]].{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} It is named after the 19th century [[Romania]]n illuminist and ethnologist [[Alecu Russo]].
==History== The original complex of buildings in the 1930s housed the financial administration, as well as three high schools (two of which were girls-only) and has the characteristic architecture of the time. The university was founded in 1946. Languages ([[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]], [[Romanian language|Romanian]], [[Russian language|Russian]], [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]]), [[mathematics]], [[physics]], some [[engineering]], [[law]], [[economics]], [[music education]], [[pedagogy]], [[sociology]], and [[psychology]] are offered at [[Bachelor]] and [[Master's degree|Master]] levels. There is a Ph.D. programme.{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} Many of its buildings have been added or re-furbished more recently. The courses and specialties are offered in Romanian, Russian, Ukrainian, and English. The university houses one of the biggest libraries in the southeastern Europe, and is an important member of the implementation of the [[Bologna process]] in Moldova.
== Faculties == Alecu Russo Balti State University faculties:<ref>[http://www.admiterea.md/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=190:universitatea-de-stat-alecu-russo-din-bli-&catid=47:admiterea2009&Itemid=69] UNIVERSITATEA de STAT „Alecu Russo” din Bălţi</ref> * Faculty of Real Sciences * Faculty of Philology * Faculty of Foreign Languages and Literatures * Faculty of Psychology and Social Work * Faculty of Sciences of Education and Arts * Faculty of Law * Faculty of Economics * Faculty of Natural Science and Agroecology
