'''Linda Secondary School''' is a [[government school]] for boys and girls in [[Livingstone, Zambia]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Schools in Livingstone, Zambia | url= http://www.zambiayp.com/category/Schools/city:Livingstone |publisher= Zambia Yp |accessdate= 7 March 2016}}</ref> It was established in 1963. The school lies about two kilometers south-east of Livingstone City.<ref>{{cite web|title= Linda High School In The News | url= https://www.lusakatimes.com/2013/06/14/the-week-in-pictures-55/ |publisher= Lusaka Times |accessdate= 7 March 2016}}</ref>. The school is known also known for winning the 2016 Copa Coca-Cola football tournament in Zambia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lusakatimes.com/2016/07/14/linda-secondary-school-wins-2016-coca-cola-football-tourney/|title=Zambia : Linda Secondary School wins 2016 Coca Cola Football Tourney|date=2016-07-14|work=LusakaTimes.com|access-date=2018-08-07|language=en-GB}}</ref> Linda High school selects Grade 7s and Grade 9s candidates from within [[Livingstone, Zambia|Livingstone]]. There is a first and second selection the first selection is for students to be coming in the morning and the second selection is for students coming in the afternoon also known as '''APU'''.
